<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-03-09T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-03-09T12:00:00-05:00" n="585" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d585">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">819.51/369: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">South</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-03-09T12:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 9,
                                        1923—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 7
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>23. Pending the negotiations for loan of $4,500,000 Government has
                            approached bankers here in regard to a loan of $100,000 for purpose of
                            continuing program of road construction. Bankers are willing to loan
                            $100,000 if Department has no objection. Reply awaited.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">South</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>